      "message": "[warning] Line 148: 🟡 Suggestion: Race condition — if `bootstrapDaemon()` is called concurrently, one thread could see `daemon.isStarted \u003d\u003d false` at line 141, then at line 149 find `bootstrapInProgress \u003d\u003d true` and return without signaling. Meanwhile, a caller of `ensureDaemonStarted()` is waiting on `bootstrapDone`. This is generally fine because the in-progress bootstrap will eventually signal, but if the first call to `bootstrapDaemon()` already completed between line 141 and 148 (daemon started by another path), `bootstrapDone` may never be set. Consider checking `daemon.isStarted` again inside the synchronized block before returning.",
